Yesterday I made an observation. I was sitting at the car shop, starring at the clock, observing how its hands moving lazily, almost teasing with its stillness. 
I kept looking at it while imagining things, thinking of how many people have been sitting at starring at it. What runs in their heads? Do people want them to move faster, slower, to not move at all? I had 47 minutes to make my mind on how fast I want the clocks hands to move. In fact, it moved too fast, I needed more of that precious careless time for my unimportant observation. 

The oil was changed. I left but the clock stayed.
